Title: Family for a day
DateModified: '2018-02-22'
DatePublished: '2018-04-20'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2018/applications/family-for-a-day
SetInCountry: Argentina
Category: The last thing I expected
AuthorName: Martina De Angelis
AuthorCountry: Italy
Text: "I ewa walking trough a little town near Iguaz\xFA falls, in Argentina. I was\
  \ with a friend of mine, and we weren\u2019t really looking for a place to eat.\
  \ But we sure were attracted by a house, there\u2019s was this salsa music playing\
  \ loud, and we stopped by to enjoy the rhythm. After a minute a little woman came\
  \ out, screaming and inviting us to lunch with her and her family. We went in, and\
  \ in the garden behind the house there were like 20 persons between brothers, sisters,\
  \ children\u2019s, dads, moms, grandparents... it was such a magical moment, because\
  \ they treated us like part of their family reunion (literally, they met that day\
  \ for the first time since the granddad had many children with different women).\
  \ We laughed hard, we ate hard, we danced, and when it was time to leave, we cried.\
  \ They made us feel loved, even just for half a day. They made us live real Argentinian\
  \ life, and we fell in love really hard with it, with them.\nI still think about\
  \ them, I have a card with their phone number, I\u2019d like to call them to tell\
  \ them i\u2019m Back in Argentina, still dreaming about their asado."
